title.narrative: By 2020, the alternative family-based care system and community-based family support services are strengthened and accessible tovulnerable children and their families.

description.narrative: UNICEF continued supporting the implementation of the national Comprehensive Programme on Ensuring the Right of the Child to Live in a Family (2020-2023).Despite the limited access to protection services during 2021 due to the ongoing double crisis, with joint efforts of theGoA, UNICEF and partner organizations, the number of children in residential care and educational institutions didn’t increase. This resulted from improvement and expansion of the coverage of community-based child/family support services and strengthening of foster care system. | Status:Met | As-of Date:21/01/2022
